# data-models

Core Data Models:

1. Campaign Model
- Hierarchical structure with parent-child relationships
- Campaign types: direct mail, digital, hybrid
- Status progression: draft -> pending -> approved -> active -> completed
- Tracks budget allocation and spend across channels
- Links to conditions, gift cards, and target audiences

2. Gift Card Pool Model 
- Multi-tier pool system:
  - Master pools (organization level)
  - Client pools (campaign specific)
- Tracks balances, usage, and reconciliation status
- Provider integrations (Tango, Giftbit, Rybbon)
- Auto-replenishment thresholds and alerts

3. Organization Model
- Three-level hierarchy:
  - Platform owner (ACE)
  - Agency organizations 
  - Client organizations
- Industry vertical classification
- Brand configuration and styling
- Gift card pool allocations

4. Campaign Conditions
- Multi-trigger condition system
- Sequential and parallel execution paths
- Action types:
  - Gift card distribution
  - SMS/email notifications
  - CRM updates
  - Webhook triggers
- Status tracking and completion rules

5. User Model
- Role-based access control
- Hierarchical permissions inheritance
- Organization-specific role assignments
- Action audit logging
- Session management

Key Relationships:
- Organizations <-> Users (many-to-many with roles)
- Campaigns <-> Conditions (one-to-many)
- Conditions <-> Gift Cards (many-to-many)
- Organizations <-> Gift Card Pools (one-to-many)

